						               													<description>House of Influence takes place in a historical age of diplomacy where influence is everything. Set after a war that has ravaged the lands people thought the golden age of peace had finally arrived. But underneath deceptive smiles the five different houses are still fighting for power and will use any means to become the house at the top: Influential people with unique skills are at the houses&amp;rsquo; disposal to win the game. Be it the selfless Martyr who will sacrifice everything to gain influence for their house, the idealistic diplomat and her silver tongue, the valiant general or other powerful roles.&amp;#10;Which house will win? A house that holds honor and valor in high regard or a house preferring the subtle tactics of a cunning Charlatan?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;House of Influence is a Team vs Team semi co-op Hidden role game where 3-10 players become members of a majority or minority. But players need to be careful, their allies might not be who you think they are. In order to accumulate the highest influence score in four rounds, the houses have up to 6 different characters at their disposal to manipulate the flow of influence and information.In this turn-based game each player rolls two available characters with their own set of abilities but can only use one to gather influence or information on the other players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The appeal of House of Influence is the quick pace of the game with easy to understand rules automated and managed by the game app and unidice - the digitized die. Replayability in this Social Deduction game of intrigue and information is guaranteed. The different houses give different advantages to their house members and the characters at their disposal - depending on the flow of the game. This Hidden Role game combines decision making with the fun of rolling a dice console in the shape of a D6.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
